B143 {'block_id': 'B143', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 143, 'start_line': 2108, 'end_line': 2109, 'raw_text': 'September 24, 2013 and September 27, 2013, Kirkland and outside counsel to Mr. MacDonald negotiated the terms of the MacDonald voting agreements, which were\nentered into by Mr. MacDonald, his wife and one of his trusts on September 27, 2013, and which became effective upon entry into the merger agreement.', 'clean_text': 'September 24, 2013 and September 27, 2013, Kirkland and outside counsel to Mr. MacDonald negotiated the terms of the MacDonald voting agreements, which were entered into by Mr. MacDonald, his wife and one of his trusts on September 27, 2013, and which became effective upon entry into the merger agreement.', 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'September 24, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-09-24', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'September 27, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-09-27', 'precision': 'exact_day'}], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B144 {'block_id': 'B144', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 144, 'start_line': 2111, 'end_line': 2111, 'raw_text': 'On', 'clean_text': 'On', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'bidding'}
B145 {'block_id': 'B145', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 145, 'start_line': 2112, 'end_line': 2114, 'raw_text': 'October 1, 2013, representatives of Mac-Gray management, along with representatives from BofA Merrill Lynch and representatives from CSC/Pamplona attended a meeting at the\nBoston offices of Goodwin Procter for purposes of conducting confirmatory business due diligence. Representatives of Mac-Gray, Goodwin Procter, BofA Merrill Lynch and representatives of CSC/Pamplona\nand Kirkland participated in various telephone conference calls over the subsequent days to finalize business and legal due diligence.', 'clean_text': 'October 1, 2013, representatives of Mac-Gray management, along with representatives from BofA Merrill Lynch and representatives from CSC/Pamplona attended a meeting at the Boston offices of Goodwin Procter for purposes of conducting confirmatory business due diligence. Representatives of Mac-Gray, Goodwin Procter, BofA Merrill Lynch and representatives of CSC/Pamplona and Kirkland participated in various telephone conference calls over the subsequent days to finalize business and legal due diligence.', 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 1, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-01', 'precision': 'exact_day'}], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'bidding'}
B146 {'block_id': 'B146', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 146, 'start_line': 2116, 'end_line': 2116, 'raw_text': 'On', 'clean_text': 'On', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 2, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B147 {'block_id': 'B147', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 147, 'start_line': 2117, 'end_line': 2119, 'raw_text': "October 5, 2013, Kirkland delivered to Goodwin Procter a revised draft of the Pamplona commitment letter which, among other things, proposed that, in addition to CSC, Pamplona\nwould be responsible in the event CSC failed to consummate the merger, but that Pamplona's liability for damages resulting from a breach of the merger agreement would be limited to an unspecified\ndollar amount.", 'clean_text': "October 5, 2013, Kirkland delivered to Goodwin Procter a revised draft of the Pamplona commitment letter which, among other things, proposed that, in addition to CSC, Pamplona would be responsible in the event CSC failed to consummate the merger, but that Pamplona's liability for damages resulting from a breach of the merger agreement would be limited to an unspecified dollar amount.", 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 5, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-05', 'precision': 'exact_day'}], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 2, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B148 {'block_id': 'B148', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 148, 'start_line': 2121, 'end_line': 2121, 'raw_text': 'On', 'clean_text': 'On', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 2, 'temporal_phase': 'bidding'}
B149 {'block_id': 'B149', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 149, 'start_line': 2122, 'end_line': 2125, 'raw_text': 'October 7, 2013, the Special Committee held a telephonic meeting, the purpose of which was to receive an update on the transaction negotiations from the Transaction Committee\nand Goodwin Procter. By invitation of the Special Committee, Mr. MacDonald was also present for a portion of the meeting. Mr. Daoust reported to the Special Committee that, after\ndiscussions between Moab and representatives of Pamplona, it was determined that Moab would not rollover any Moab shares in the transaction. Mr. Daoust also provided the Special Committee with\nan overview of the open business points and the progress the parties had made since the September 23 rd', 'clean_text': 'October 7, 2013, the Special Committee held a telephonic meeting, the purpose of which was to receive an update on the transaction negotiations from the Transaction Committee and Goodwin Procter. By invitation of the Special Committee, Mr. MacDonald was also present for a portion of the meeting. Mr. Daoust reported to the Special Committee that, after discussions between Moab and representatives of Pamplona, it was determined that Moab would not rollover any Moab shares in the transaction. Mr. Daoust also provided the Special Committee with an overview of the open business points and the progress the parties had made since the September 23 rd', 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 7, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-07', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'September', 'normalized': None, 'precision': 'unknown'}], 'entity_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'Special Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}, {'raw_text': 'Transaction Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}], 'evidence_density': 2, 'temporal_phase': 'bidding'}
B150 {'block_id': 'B150', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 150, 'start_line': 2127, 'end_line': 2127, 'raw_text': 'Also', 'clean_text': 'Also', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B151 {'block_id': 'B151', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 151, 'start_line': 2128, 'end_line': 2129, 'raw_text': 'on October 7, 2013, Kirkland delivered to Goodwin Procter a revised draft of the merger agreement which, among other things, proposed a $15 million Mac-Gray\ntermination fee, which represented approximately 4.4% of the total equity value of the transaction, and certain positions on the scope of various post-signing covenants.', 'clean_text': 'on October 7, 2013, Kirkland delivered to Goodwin Procter a revised draft of the merger agreement which, among other things, proposed a $15 million Mac-Gray termination fee, which represented approximately 4.4% of the total equity value of the transaction, and certain positions on the scope of various post-signing covenants.', 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 7, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-07', 'precision': 'exact_day'}], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B152 {'block_id': 'B152', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 152, 'start_line': 2131, 'end_line': 2131, 'raw_text': 'On', 'clean_text': 'On', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 4, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B153 {'block_id': 'B153', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 153, 'start_line': 2132, 'end_line': 2137, 'raw_text': "October 8, 2013, representatives from Goodwin Procter and Kirkland participated in a telephone conference call to discuss the open points in the merger agreement and the\nPamplona commitment letter, including to what extent Pamplona would also have liability in the event CSC failed to consummate the merger, which Kirkland proposed, at the direction of CSC/Pamplona, be\ncapped at $50 million. Kirkland and Goodwin Procter also discussed CSC's and Pamplona's liability for damages resulting from a breach of the merger agreement, certain post-signing covenants and\nthe parties' termination rights, including the amounts of the Mac-Gray termination fee and the CSC reverse termination fee. The parties also discussed potential compromises on the post-signing\ncovenants. Goodwin Procter and Kirkland agreed to communicate these positions to their respective clients. Later that day, after various discussions among representatives from CSC/Pamplona, Kirkland,\nGoodwin Procter and the members of the Transaction Committee, and on behalf of the Special Committee, Goodwin Procter sent an e-mail to the representatives of Kirkland that proposed to accept the", 'clean_text': "October 8, 2013, representatives from Goodwin Procter and Kirkland participated in a telephone conference call to discuss the open points in the merger agreement and the Pamplona commitment letter, including to what extent Pamplona would also have liability in the event CSC failed to consummate the merger, which Kirkland proposed, at the direction of CSC/Pamplona, be capped at $50 million. Kirkland and Goodwin Procter also discussed CSC's and Pamplona's liability for damages resulting from a breach of the merger agreement, certain post-signing covenants and the parties' termination rights, including the amounts of the Mac-Gray termination fee and the CSC reverse termination fee. The parties also discussed potential compromises on the post-signing covenants. Goodwin Procter and Kirkland agreed to communicate these positions to their respective clients. Later that day, after various discussions among representatives from CSC/Pamplona, Kirkland, Goodwin Procter and the members of the Transaction Committee, and on behalf of the Special Committee, Goodwin Procter sent an e-mail to the representatives of Kirkland that proposed to accept the", 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 8, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-08', 'precision': 'exact_day'}], 'entity_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'Special Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}, {'raw_text': 'Transaction Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}], 'evidence_density': 4, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B154 {'block_id': 'B154', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 154, 'start_line': 2139, 'end_line': 2139, 'raw_text': '39', 'clean_text': '39', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 0, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B155 {'block_id': 'B155', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 155, 'start_line': 2142, 'end_line': 2143, 'raw_text': '$50 million\nliability cap proposed by Pamplona and proposed a $10.5 million Mac-Gray termination fee, which represented approximately 3.0% of the total equity value of the transaction.', 'clean_text': '$50 million liability cap proposed by Pamplona and proposed a $10.5 million Mac-Gray termination fee, which represented approximately 3.0% of the total equity value of the transaction.', 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 2, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B156 {'block_id': 'B156', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 156, 'start_line': 2145, 'end_line': 2145, 'raw_text': 'On', 'clean_text': 'On', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B157 {'block_id': 'B157', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 157, 'start_line': 2146, 'end_line': 2148, 'raw_text': "October 9, 2013, in follow up to the October 8, 2013 negotiations and proposals made by Goodwin Procter, the members of the Transaction Committee participated in a\ntelephone conference call with a representative from CSC/Pamplona to discuss the open issues in the merger agreement, including certain post-signing covenants and the parties' termination rights,\nincluding the amounts of the Mac-Gray termination fee and the CSC reverse termination fee, but did not reach agreement on these issues.", 'clean_text': "October 9, 2013, in follow up to the October 8, 2013 negotiations and proposals made by Goodwin Procter, the members of the Transaction Committee participated in a telephone conference call with a representative from CSC/Pamplona to discuss the open issues in the merger agreement, including certain post-signing covenants and the parties' termination rights, including the amounts of the Mac-Gray termination fee and the CSC reverse termination fee, but did not reach agreement on these issues.", 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 9, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-09', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'October 8, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-08', 'precision': 'exact_day'}], 'entity_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'Transaction Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B158 {'block_id': 'B158', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 158, 'start_line': 2150, 'end_line': 2150, 'raw_text': 'Later', 'clean_text': 'Later', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 5, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B159 {'block_id': 'B159', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 159, 'start_line': 2151, 'end_line': 2158, 'raw_text': "on October 9, 2013, the Special Committee held a telephonic meeting, the purpose of which was to receive an update on the transaction negotiations from the Transaction\nCommittee and Goodwin Procter. By invitation of the Special Committee, Mr. MacDonald was also present at this meeting. The Transaction Committee reported to the Special Committee on the\nnegotiations that had taken place since the meeting of the Special Committee held on October 7, 2013. The Transaction Committee reported that the parties had come to an agreement that\nPamplona's liability for certain damages would be limited to $50 million, but that certain post-signing covenants and the amounts of the termination fees remained open issues. The Special\nCommittee discussed various alternatives that could be proposed to CSC/Pamplona on the open issues. Goodwin Procter then reported that Kirkland had requested on behalf of CSC/Pamplona that the\nexclusivity agreement, due to expire at 5 p. m. ET on October 12, 2013, be extended to allow for continued negotiations of these open issues. After discussion, the Special Committee\nauthorized the Transaction Committee to negotiate the open issues within certain parameters and in connection therewith to extend exclusivity to October 15, 2013. The Special Committee also\ndetermined to reconvene for an update telephone conference call on October 11, 2013.", 'clean_text': "on October 9, 2013, the Special Committee held a telephonic meeting, the purpose of which was to receive an update on the transaction negotiations from the Transaction Committee and Goodwin Procter. By invitation of the Special Committee, Mr. MacDonald was also present at this meeting. The Transaction Committee reported to the Special Committee on the negotiations that had taken place since the meeting of the Special Committee held on October 7, 2013. The Transaction Committee reported that the parties had come to an agreement that Pamplona's liability for certain damages would be limited to $50 million, but that certain post-signing covenants and the amounts of the termination fees remained open issues. The Special Committee discussed various alternatives that could be proposed to CSC/Pamplona on the open issues. Goodwin Procter then reported that Kirkland had requested on behalf of CSC/Pamplona that the exclusivity agreement, due to expire at 5 p. m. ET on October 12, 2013, be extended to allow for continued negotiations of these open issues. After discussion, the Special Committee authorized the Transaction Committee to negotiate the open issues within certain parameters and in connection therewith to extend exclusivity to October 15, 2013. The Special Committee also determined to reconvene for an update telephone conference call on October 11, 2013.", 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 9, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-09', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'October 7, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-07', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'October 12, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-12', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'October 15, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-15', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'October 11, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-11', 'precision': 'exact_day'}], 'entity_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'Special Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}, {'raw_text': 'Transaction Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}], 'evidence_density': 5, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B160 {'block_id': 'B160', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 160, 'start_line': 2160, 'end_line': 2160, 'raw_text': 'On', 'clean_text': 'On', 'is_heading': True, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [], 'entity_mentions': [], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
B161 {'block_id': 'B161', 'document_id': '0001047469-13-010973', 'ordinal': 161, 'start_line': 2161, 'end_line': 2165, 'raw_text': 'October 10, 2013, the members of the Transaction Committee and the representative of CSC/Pamplona engaged in various discussions regarding the open issues, including certain\npost-signing covenants and the amounts of the termination fees. While the parties reached a compromise on the post-signing covenants, no agreement was reached on the amount of the Mac-Gray termination\nfee. On October 11, 2013, the Special Committee held a telephonic meeting to discuss the proposed terms of the transaction and the status of discussions with CSC/Pamplona. By invitation of the\nSpecial Committee, Mr. Rothenberg and representatives of Goodwin Procter were also present. The members of the Transaction Committee reviewed with the Special Committee the negotiations that\nhad taken place with representatives from CSC/Pamplona since the October 9 th th', 'clean_text': 'October 10, 2013, the members of the Transaction Committee and the representative of CSC/Pamplona engaged in various discussions regarding the open issues, including certain post-signing covenants and the amounts of the termination fees. While the parties reached a compromise on the post-signing covenants, no agreement was reached on the amount of the Mac-Gray termination fee. On October 11, 2013, the Special Committee held a telephonic meeting to discuss the proposed terms of the transaction and the status of discussions with CSC/Pamplona. By invitation of the Special Committee, Mr. Rothenberg and representatives of Goodwin Procter were also present. The members of the Transaction Committee reviewed with the Special Committee the negotiations that had taken place with representatives from CSC/Pamplona since the October 9 th th', 'is_heading': False, 'page_break_before': False, 'page_break_after': False, 'date_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'October 10, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-10', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'October 11, 2013', 'normalized': '2013-10-11', 'precision': 'exact_day'}, {'raw_text': 'October', 'normalized': None, 'precision': 'unknown'}], 'entity_mentions': [{'raw_text': 'Special Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}, {'raw_text': 'Transaction Committee', 'entity_type': 'committee'}], 'evidence_density': 3, 'temporal_phase': 'outcome'}
